<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920207-0081</DOCNO><DOCID>920207-0081.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Gantos Inc.:   January Sales Climbed 19%;   Same-Store Sales Rose 21%</HL><DATE>02/07/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   GTOS</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>ALL SPECIALTY RETAILERS (RTS)SPECIALTY APPAREL RETAILERS (SAP)</IN><RE>MICHIGAN (MI)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Gantos Inc., Grand Rapids, Mich., reported sales of $14.8million in January, a 19% increase over sales of $12.5million during the year-earlier period. Same-store sales rose21%.   The women's apparel retailer said its fourth-quarter salesrose 12% to $78.8 million from $70.3 million during the sameperiod last year. Same-store sales increased 14%.</LP><TEXT>   Sales for the year ended Feb. 1 rose 5% to $257.9 millionfrom $246.3 million during the year-ago period. Same-storesales increased 1%.   All sales figures have been adjusted to exclude net salesfrom catalog operations, which were discontinued during thefirst quarter of 1991.</TEXT></DOC>